        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29106",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Based on the documentation you are referring to:\n\n{quote}\nLimitation \nThe current implementation of Zend_File_Transfer is limited to HTTP Post Uploads. Other adapters supporting downloads and other protocols will be added in future releases. Unimplemented methods will throw an exception. For now, you should use Zend_File_Transfer_Adapter_Http directly. As soon as there are multiple adapters available you can use a common interface. \n{quote}\n\nAnd also the example in the manual reads:\n\n{quote}\n$adapter = new Zend_File_Transfer_Adapter_Http();$adapter->setDestination('C:\\temp');if (!$adapter->receive()) {    $messages = $adapter->getMessages();    echo implode(\"\\n\", $messages);}\n{quote}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-26T04:23:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-26T04:23:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29521",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi thomas,\n\nchristian clearly stated a still existing error, the documentated methods getFileSize and getMimeType do _NOT_ exists.\n\nPlease look into it.\n\nThanks, Littlex :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-17T09:29:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-17T09:29:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29522",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The methods getFileSize and getMimeType, as stated in the documentation, do not exist.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-17T09:36:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-17T09:36:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29523",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "They exist within Zend_File_Transfer_Adapter_Abstract since r13822 and r13935.\n\nAs we are not allowed to add new functionality within a mini-release they will be released with the next minor release as all new functionalities.\n\nSo the only real failure I see it a false assignment of the fix release.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-17T11:19:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-17T11:19:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29524",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As side note:\nThe problem of the manual itself is part of a new proposal which I am working on with Mickael.\n\nBut this has nothing to do with this issue.",
